        <introduction>
            <para>
                This section explains how to build custom assets (e.g. models, effects)
                and where to find pre-built assets (shaders, textures),
                which are required by DigitalRise Graphics at runtime.
            </para>
        </introduction>

        
        <section address="Start">
            <title>Getting started</title>
            <content>
                <para>
                    This documentation assumes that you are familiar with the XNA Content Pipeline
                    and that you already know how to create a content project. If you are new to this 
                    topic, you may want to look at the XNA documentation first:
                </para>
                <list class="bullet">
                    <listItem>
                        <externalLink>
                            <linkText>XNA Game Studio: Adding Art, Music, and Other Game Assets</linkText>
                            <linkUri>https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/dd282477.aspx</linkUri>
                        </externalLink>
                    </listItem>
                    <listItem>
                        <externalLink>
                            <linkText>MonoGame: Adding Art, Sounds, and More</linkText>
                            <linkUri>http://www.monogame.net/documentation/?page=Adding_Art_Sounds_and_More</linkUri>
                        </externalLink>
                    </listItem>
                </list>
            </content>
        </section>

        
